cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Agent Memory Guard in academic or technical work, please cite it as below."
title: "OWASP Agent Memory Guard: A Runtime Defense and Open Benchmark for Memory Poisoning in LLM Agents (ASI06)"
abstract: >-
  Agent Memory Guard is the OWASP reference implementation for ASI06 (Memory
  Poisoning). It is a runtime defense layer that mediates every read and write
  to an LLM agent's persistent memory through composable detectors and a
  declarative policy engine, with source-class provenance, structured forensic
  events, and point-in-time snapshot rollback. The project includes an open
  benchmark of attack and benign payloads for evaluating memory-integrity
  defenses.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Vaishnavi
    family-names: Gudur
    affiliation: "OWASP Agent Memory Guard Project"
repository-code: "https://github.com/OWASP/www-project-agent-memory-guard"
url: "https://owasp.org/www-project-agent-memory-guard/"
license: Apache-2.0
version: "0.2.2"
keywords:
  - LLM agents
  - agent security
  - memory poisoning
  - prompt injection
  - OWASP
  - ASI06
  - runtime defense
  - benchmark

